      • seek

        public void seek()
        Description copied from class: TagPayloadReader
        Notifies the reader that a seek has occurred.

        Following a call to this method, the data passed to the next invocation of TagPayloadReader.consume(ParsableByteArray, long) will not be a continuation of the data that was previously passed. Hence the reader should reset any internal state.

        Specified by:
        seek in class TagPayloadReader
